value.0: Third in a series of defensive automatons created by the tinkerers of the Mak'a'nor Mining Company.
Fourth in the series of defensive automatons designed by famed Gnomish tinkerers.

The common Badger is a small but fierce mammal. Its strong forelimbs are armed with long claws, used for both digging and self-defense.  They are very important in svirfnebli communities as a food source, guard animals and even family pets.  This particular badger seems to study you with very intelligent eyes.
Third in a series of defensive automatons created by tinkerers of the Mak'a'nor Mining Company.

This heavy iron and stone gate stands firm against all but the most determined assaults.  Crafted with the expert skill of the svirfnebli, it guards the town of Mak'a'nor against incursions from the evil races of the underdark.
An old brass nameplate on the door reads simply, "Pollo."
A badly worn iron name plate on the door reads, "Jak Dugget."  A foul smell emerges from within.
A brass nameplate in the door reads, "Zincalinca Chortlechuckle"
A large gilded steel nameplate reads, "Gravel Orebearer, Orebearer Mining Co."  There does not appear to be anyone inside.
A bright silver nameplate on the door reads, "Drugrigrin Roido"

Mak'a'nor Mining Company

For employment or consignment opportunities inquire within
The lamp post is pitted and scarred by the harsh night air.

This memorial commemorates the svirfnebli who fled Gibbelmethin and resettled the trading outpost of Mak'a'nor.  Dedicated in memory to those who fled the city and gave their life in the defense of Mak'a'nor.  May they and all of that famed city rest in the Golden Hills forever.
The torch paints its environs in warmer hues. You find yourself grateful for its glow.

Mak'a'nor Workshops

Chief Tradesperson:  Tincture Tinkerflame

Welcome to the Dormouse tavern

This bag contains cosmetics, hair dye, and small physical props. The kit is the perfect tool for disguise and provides a +2 circumstance bonus on disguise checks. A disguise kit is exhausted after one ten uses.

A polished steel mirror is handy when you want to look around corners, signal friends with reflected sunlight, keep an eye on a medusa, and make sure that you look good enough to present yourself to the queen, or examine wounds that you've received on hard-to-see parts of your body.

When a wall doesn't offer any handholds and footholds, you can make your own. They can also be used to secure a door open or shut. A piton is a steel spike with an eye through which you can loop a rope. They need a small hammer to drive them.

Multi use baking flour.

This is a water canteen. No adventurer should be without one.

Target a source of water to fill the canteen, or target the ground near you while you are standing next to water.

This large, bulky contraption uses the regulated flow of droplets of water to measure the passing of time. It can fairly accurately measure two hours before it needs to be reset.

*This item is intended for role-play purposes only*
This is a bedroll.  You can use it by placing it on the ground.
This is a bedroll, to use it, drop it on the ground.

Greenfish are abundant in the seas that lap the coast of Nordock. While bland themselves, a concoction of pepper and other spices brings out a surprisingly tangy and pleasant flavor. This fish counts as a single food serving for resting purposes.
This is a healing kit, used by those with skill, to stop the bleeding and stabilize patients.
A flask of acid that can be thrown at enemies.
Alchemist's Fire is a sticky, adhesive substance that ignites on contact with air.
